Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.122, 15, which does not reflect BM 2011,5002.143. Name, Teisagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0214.25.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1076)
